    "As a Lead Author of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) Assessment, he contributed to the 2007 Nobel Peace Prize, which was awarded jointly to IPCC and Al Gore, Jr.",
    "He received the 2012 Vening Meinesz Medal from the European Geosciences Union.",
    "His research focuses on interdisciplinary satellite geodesy and Earth Sciences, including sea-level and climate science, precision orbit determination, gravity field modeling, and deep-learning based climate-induced hazards monitoring.",
    "He has published over 379 refereed journal articles and book chapters, with Google Scholar citations of 21,312, h-index of 68, and i-10 Index of 255.",
    "As an Earth Scientist, he has a World Ranking of 1,192, and a National Ranking of 583.Fig. 1.1Fig."
